<seg id=1> China's Insurance Supervision Management Project Was Started in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Beijing, January 21(xinhua)- A research project was started the other day in Beijing on how to assist People's Bank of China to supervise the insurance rules set by foreign invested insurance companies and what is the standardized insurance system. </seg>
<seg id=3> This project is a joint venture invested by Britain Royal Sun United Insurance Group Company and America Lincoln National Group Company with total investment of 1.4 million US dollars. America Everway Acountants' undertook the practicing of this project. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This insurance supervision project will make a systematic study in reference to foreign advanced experiences on foreign funds insurance in China and current regulations of insurance control, and will work out a constructive research program beneficial for China's insurance supervision development and improvement of supervision rules and regulations. </seg>
<seg id=5> In addition, this project is to make deeper studies on better control of those institutions and operation procedures on the basis of the current regulations on foreign funded insurance institutions issued by the People's Bank of China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is revealed that the new supervision regulations certainly will be beneficial for the build-up of a better system of foreign insurance institutions management and will help the People's Bank of China for a stronger control over the insurance market. </seg>
</p>
